2011-10-19T07:21:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-19/bank-of-thailand-s-monetary-policy-history-summary-table-.html
The following table is a historical
summary of the Bank of  Thailand ’s monetary policy decisions.  The Bank of Thailand targets the 1-day repurchase rate.  Since Bloomberg started surveys for Bank of Thailand’s
repurchase rate in September of 2003, there have been a total
of 66 rate decisions by the bank, of which 11 were unexpected,
resulting in the survey matching the actual rate decision 83.3%
of the time.  To contact the reporter on this story:
